actions.comment:
Thanks for the thorough report with platform-specific details and screenshots.

Here's a workaround you can use while we investigate: convert the bitmap to sRGB before assigning it to `SKBitmapImageSource`:

```csharp
var displayInfo = new SKImageInfo(bitmap.Width, bitmap.Height,
    SKImageInfo.PlatformColorType,
    SKAlphaType.Premul,
    SKColorSpace.CreateSrgb());
var displayBitmap = new SKBitmap(displayInfo);
using (var canvas = new SKCanvas(displayBitmap))
{
    canvas.DrawBitmap(bitmap, 0, 0);
}
var imageSource = new SKBitmapImageSource { Bitmap = displayBitmap };
```

The root cause is that the platform conversion methods (`ToWriteableBitmap`, `ToBitmap`, `ToUIImage`) create a destination `SKImageInfo` with no color space, so `ReadPixels` copies raw pixel values without color space conversion. On Apple, `ToCGImage` additionally hardcodes an RGBA pixel format assumption that doesn't match non-RGBA bitmaps, which explains the broader color type issues on macOS/iOS.

This is related to #2354 (same color space unawareness in `GetPixel`).

Note: `SKBitmapImageSource` is MAUI-specific. For WPF, apply the same bitmap conversion before calling `ToWriteableBitmap()`.
